#. type: \b; header
#: ../help/help.E.txt:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do Programmers Need to Know Math?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../help/help.E.txt:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "The answer is: it depends on what you want to do."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../help/help.E.txt:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Many programmers should feel at least a little bit comfortably with math up to high school level. This should be fairly enough to get a lot of stuff done. Most of the school material might not be necessary, but better to know more than less, don't you think? You never know when being able to solve a quadratic equation might come in handy. If you aren't a high school graduate yet, don't worry. You still have time, just don't take math classes too lightly. Treat them at least like a training of logical and abstract thinking, of being able to solve problems, which is obviously important in programming."
msgstr ""

#. type: \b; header
#: ../help/help.E.txt:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "When Math Is Crucial"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../help/help.E.txt:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "You might even want to make a step further. In universities they teach you some really hard high-level math, yet Computer Science wouldn't exist without it. Algorithms are complicated and it is important for a computer scientist to be able to tell how long an algorithm will be running, to prove if it is correct or to just get an idea how to solve a hard problem, like finding the shortest path (which is not that trivial as you might think)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../help/help.E.txt:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "We don't want to scare you. You can be a decent programmer without doing more complicated calculations than addition, subtraction, multiplication and division. In this course though, we will try to teach you some math when it's necessary. This is not a math course, but you'll see that math has many applications in programming. Especially geometry and trigonometry is useful in Colobot. The more you know, the better. You might be surprised how math synergizes well with programming."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../help/help.E.txt:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Remember that programming languages like CBOT are only tools to get a job done. We want you to learn how to program, not only how to use CBOT. If you know a concept, you won't have much problems to adapt to a different tool with this concept, maybe a language like C++ or Java."
msgstr ""

