#. type: Plain text
#: ../help/help.E.txt:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Math is especially needed in graphics-related software, video games, robotics, cryptography and so on. You can't know physics without math. Even when you are creating a simple Graphical User Interface (GUI) or a website, you might need to do some simple calculations in order to get a GUI element, like a button, properly positioned. Most importantly, you won't get away from math if you want to create your SuperEfficientAndEffectiveAlienKillingProgram, although a simpler program might be sufficient for you, so yeah, the answer to the question is ambigous indeed."
msgstr ""
